Objects in php

LIke JSON Objects but different syntax. 

Using data in PHP
With almost all coding languages we can store data about something (e.g. a post or image) in an object. An object is a container of related data.

Weâ€™ll be using the same idea later on when we build our gallery, getting the caption and size info for our images which are stored in objects.

// here we have an object called $lawrence
$lawrence = array(
  first_name  => 'Lawrence',
  last_name => 'Gosset',
  location => 'London',
  age => 27
);

echo $lawrence['location']
// gives us 'London'

